<paragraph blockId="17.[590,1304,1510,1933]" pageId="17" pageNumber="725">
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="725" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="725" startId="17.[712,892,1782,1815]" targetBox="[448,452,2506,2527]" targetPageId="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[712,896,1782,1815]" pageId="17" pageNumber="725">Distribution.</emphasis>
SW Philippines, in S Palawan I.
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="725" type="description">
Fab notes. Head-body mean 183 mm (males) and 163 mm (females), 
<paragraph blockId="17.[100,1306,1944,2527]" pageId="17" pageNumber="725">tail mean 140 mm sles and 135 mm (females); weight mean 163 g. The Palawan Montane Squirrel is brown on dorsum and gray on venter. Ventral hair has light buff tips.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection box="[102,745,2020,2053]" pageId="17" pageNumber="725" type="biology_ecology">
